<div class="container" id="home">
    <h2>Overview</h2>
    <p>Join us on an epic adventure from the lowest point in North America, Badwater Basin, to the highest, Mount Whitney. This two-day journey combines a grueling bike ride and a challenging hike, taking us from the depths of Death Valley to the heights of the Sierra Nevada.</p>
</div>

<div class="container" id="itinerary">
    <h2>Itinerary</h2>
    <h3>Day 1: October 19 - Bike Ride</h3>
    <p>Start early morning at Badwater Basin and ride approximately 135 miles to Whitney Portal, gaining around 14,600 feet in elevation.</p>
    
    <h3>Day 2: October 20 - Hike</h3>
    <p>Hike the regular trail to Mount Whitney's summit, covering 22 miles round trip with an elevation gain of 6,200 feet.</p>
</div>

<div class="container" id="weather">
    <h2>Weather & Packing</h2>
    <div class="weather">
        <h3>Weather Forecast</h3>
        <p><strong>Death Valley:</strong> Early morning 55–65°F, Late morning 70–80°F.</p>
        <p><strong>Mount Whitney:</strong> Early morning 15–40°F (varies by elevation), expect colder temperatures at higher altitudes.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="packing">
        <h3>Packing List</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Bike gear: Helmet, repair kit, lights</li>
            <li>Hiking gear: Boots, trekking poles, layers</li>
            <li>Food & Water: 3-4 liters of water, high-calorie snacks</li>
            <li>Safety: First aid kit, emergency blanket</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="container" id="maps">
    <h2>Maps</h2>
